rComments: Spanish is my favorite subject and area of study, but this was my least favorite class because of the teacher. She runs around the classroom and literally screams at you and calls on students, putting them on the spot. Directions aren't clear about assignments nor are her grading methods. Overall I was not impressed by her method of teaching.

This class was definitely difficult, but I was surprised that I ended up with a B+...thought I had an A in the bag! She definitely puts a lot more weight on the oral presentations and participation than I had banked on. Tests aren't too bad, just make sure to study the vocab.

Brenda is an amazing teacher!! Her class was the most challenging Spanish class I've taken so far, but it helped me learn a lot and increased my fluency. If you really wanna learn, take her class. Whoever gave her a bad rating is just mad they didn't study for the tests...if you study and really put the work in, you'll do great.

Its a hard class, and Brenda lets you know this crucial fact from day one. ALOT of work--incorporates lectures, textbook material, and movies so pay attention! If you're looking for an easy A, avoid Brenda because if you don't put in the effort you get a C+ like me...this is a correction to the previous comment because I put "Writ 2" by mistake!!

Its a hard class, and Brenda lets you know this crucial fact from day one. ALOT of work--incorporates lectures, textbook material, and movies so pay attention! If you're looking for an easy A, avoid Brenda because if you don't put in the effort you get a C+ like me...

Second time taking Brenda's class, and I enjoyed it even more than the first time.  Maybe it's just because I've had more practice, but I didn't feel like I was put on the spot as much in her class - even though I was.  The class was pretty good overall - just study for the exams, come to class and participate, and you'll do fine.
If you like memorizing a bunch of words then this is the class for you. If you're like me, it was pointless as I remember absolutely nothing from this class.

Assignments are tedious and repetitive, but easy. Don't miss class, as EVERYTHING from lecture is fair game on exams (frequent). Much of the material comes from videos which are shown only once. Don't expect 156 to be like one of the grammar classes, cuz it's not.

Really enjoyed my class with Brenda.  I learned a ton in class, and I know my fluency increased greatly.  Definitely not an easy teacher, but I thought she was quite fair with the way she graded.  Doesn't fail people because she wants to; she simply wants to be sure they're ready to go to the next level fully prepared.  If you can, take her class!!

Barcelo is an excellent professor who involves the class in her teaching, and through the interaction, enhances your understanding of the material. I would definitely recommend her, she's a lot of fun, full of energy, and is way better than the average lecturer. If you put the time in, you'll get a lot out!

She has her favorites, and she is extremely rude. She makes the students put on skits to teach material she should be teaching. She puts you on the spot whenever she has the chance, grades very hard, and is an overall horrible teacher.  I loathe Spanish class because I have to listen to her shrill voice.  She should be fired!

Good professors teach you mechanisms to memorize material, but she does NOT.  However, she does give you all the material you need.  She was only sometimes helpful in answering student questions.  She also has students do things for her they shouldn't, using them. Though she is nice, fun and organized, her grading is unfair(policy on syllabus lies)

This class was way easy. Everything is basically memorizing straight out of her reader, including the oral presentation and exams. No final, just an easy research paper and equally simple partner-oral exam. Very energetic woman, sometimes a little too much, but keeps you alert at least...
Class was never boring. There was never any busywork. Take any class that she teaches.

Brenda's wonderful. She's clear, helpful, and extremely engaging. She obviously cares loads about the students and their education, and while demanding, she lets you know what's expected and motivates you to do it.
brenda was an amazing teacher! my fluency greatly increased when i took her class... she is excited about teaching, and it shows..highly energetic and makes the class fly by...
No Comments

Brenda really focuses on making you familiar with spanish. she wants to make sure you can speak the language not just memorize the critiria. she mixes in culture to make learning fun! shes awesome if you ask me!

Brenda is an amazing teacher. I took Spanish 2 and 3 with her even though they were at the least desirable times to have a class. I never felt like I wasted my time in her classes. Class attendance is a must especially if you are there to learn not just get a good grade. She's also a really fun teacher to have as well as charismatic.

she is a very good teacher who doesnt waste anybody's time with nonsense work. every class you can say you have learned something new and the tests are exactly like the practices excercises in class. she is always there to help at her office hours. i got a good grade and good evaluation. A+ teacher.
She was a great teacher. I learned so much and my Spanish improved a lot.  I actually liked going to her class and she made me want to continue taking Spanish

Brenda was an excellent teacher.  She "doesn't like busywork" and doesn't give any homework that she collects- just suggestions for homework.  If you pay attention you will learn a lot.  Also, you get tons of practice speaking in Spanish so that by the end your Spanish has really improved.
not helpful at all..plays favorites.. WILL fail you if you dont read instructions on the exams.. horrible..i'll never take another spanish class again because of her
I felt my Spanish improved a lot due to this class.  She was a really fun and excellent teacher
She was very enthusiastic and energetic.  I liked her a lot and her classes were nice because she tried to include everyone in conversation, which is helpful even though its kind of nerve racking.

Very unhelpful to me when I needed it. She had her teachers pets and those were the only people she cared about. Her teaching made me not want to be in the class or even try to take spanish classes again. Cruel and unusual evaluations.
Greatest teacher ever.  Made everything approchable.  Very helpful in and out of class.  Take her class!!!!!

Great professor. Very helpful, willing to challenge students. Sometimes moves a little too fast, but is easy to talk to outside class, and very willing to assist students. Great professor, she's lovely.
